Sentencas: GdBaCo2O5+delta (GBCO)/poly (vinyl pyrrolidone) (PVP) composite nanofibers were prepared by electrospinning.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: Structural and morphological evolution of the GBCO/PVP fibers under calcinations at various temperatures was studied.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: Using 600 degrees C pre-calcined GBCO/PVP composite nanofibers, pure phase GBCO cathode with homogeneous network structure was easily fabricated on Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: The as-prepared GBCO cathode was characterized by electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS) measurements based on a GBCO/GDC/GBCO symmetric cell.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: Its electrochemical performance was compared with the cathode prepared with the GBCO powders synthesized with sol-gel method.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: The GBCO cathode fabricated using GBCO/PVP composite fibers had area specific resistances (ASRs) of 0.53 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C, 0.22 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C, 0.10 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C and 0.043 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C respectively, which are lower than ASR results of the GBCO cathode prepared with powders.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance

Sentencas: The results have demonstrated that the GBCO cathode fabricated using electrospun composite nanofibers has significantly enhanced electrochemical activities for oxygen reduction reaction, and it can serve as a promising cathode material for intermediate- temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Fabrication of GdBaCo2O5+δ cathode using electrospun composite nanofibers and its improved electrochemical performance
